HEADWORD: Hostry
<hw>Host"ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>hosterie</ets>, <ets>osterie</ets>, OF. <ets>hosterie</ets>. See
<er>Host</er> a landlord.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A hostelry; an inn or
lodging house.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Marlowe.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A stable for horses.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Johnson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hot</ent>⟦br⟧
